ems sound. You may be surprised at what a big difference some minor adjustments can make.</span>\n\n<b style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">#10. Follow up</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It’s hard to overstate the importance of this step. Failing to follow up and follow through on commitments you make to prospects can be tremendously costly. Keep ALL appointments. Respond promptly. Supply any promised information.  This is part of earning trust.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Research has repeatedly shown that it’s necessary to make contact multiple times before a prospect becomes a client. Sales experts</span><a href=\"https://www.salesforce.com/blog/2015/04/takes-6-8-touches-generate-viable-sales-lead-heres-why-gp.html\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">hold</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> that you must reach the lead at least 7 times on average before a sale. This varies widely depending on the situation and the format and quality of the contact, but there is no doubt that your first call should never be your last.</span>','10 Actionable Tips for CRE Agents New to Prospecting','','publish','open','closed','','10-actionable-tips-for-cre-agents-new-to-prospecting','','','2016-07-05 11:58:09','2016-07-05 11:58:09','',0,'http://wordpress.list-trac.com//?p=1003',0,'post','',0),
