	(1671,4,'2017-04-23 02:15:57','2017-04-23 02:15:57','<h2>Company Description</h2>\nCome help us change the real estate industry! We are a venture backed, profitable, high growth company that provides analytics on over 100 million properties to predict which properties are most likely to sell or refinance. We have over two thousand customers including fortune 500 companies as well as commercial real estate agents, lenders, and investors. If you want to be part of an explosive growth and entrepreneurial environment, this is a tremendous opportunity. ProspectNow also has a great working environment and located right downtown in Los Altos. You will be a key player at a fast growing company, you will be challenged and you will have a lot of fun along the way. Come join the ProspectNow Team!\n\nTo learn more about what it\'s like to work at ProspectNow, take a look at our stack overflow page: <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/jobs/companies/prospectnow\">http://stackoverflow.com/jobs/companies/prospectnow</a>\n<h2>Job Description</h2>\nThis position represents a tremendous opportunity to have a major impact on a fast growing and really cool real estate website called ProspectNow. We are tracking over 100 million properties and provide detailed analytics for the real estate community. If you are the right candidate, you will have an opportunity to help with performance, scalability, and usability. You will report to and work closely with the CEO as well as be a team lead for the other engineers. Our product is built on the LAMP stack and we are currently migrating to AWS elastic bean stalk and RDS. As a part of this migration, we are reviewing frameworks and platforms to further optimize the application.\n\nWe have recently implemented SCRUM along with a migration from SVN to Git and bit-bucket. So an understanding of SCRUM and branching etc is a requirement.\n\nBecause this is a team lead role (and ultimately could grow into a management position), your ability to communicate and help motivate the team are critical. We are looking for someone with an unbridled passion for software development. This position is in Los Altos, Ca. Remote positions are not being considered at this time however relocation assistance may be provided for the right candidate.\n\nHere are a few examples of engineering situations you would deal with:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Importing 10GB fixed with text files into a mysql database efficiently on a weekly basis and then running post processing scripts to calculate and derive new fields from the data. E.g. count the number of properties an owner owns or calculate the average value in a zip code.</li>\n 	<li>Aggregate properties from multiple data-sources with different address formats and cross reference by address</li>\n 	<li>Calculating analytics from a group of properties on a map enclosed in a series of polygon points dynamically. E.g. display a pie chart of properties by type</li>\n 	<li>Build entirely new UI on top of our internal API based on Sketch images using HTML, angular/react.js and CSS.</li>\n</ol>\nand any more...\n\nProspectNow is a profitable and growing enterprise, so we are not dependent on raising more money to continue to do what we do. We are confident we can accelerate from double digit growth to triple digit with the addition of the right features.\n\nThis position may be a contract job to start, or we might do a full time role depending on the candidate.\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Extensive knowledge of AWS</li>\n 	<li>Solid understanding of SCRUM and Git</li>\n 	<li>Extensive database knowldege including Amazon RDS and databases over 1TB</li>\n 	<li>Experience using CSS, HTML5, Linux, PHP, Mysql, JavaScript and familiarity with AngularJS</li>\n 	<li>Experience with frameworks including Twitter-bootstrap</li>\n 	<li>Experience working with distributed APIs such as google maps</li>\n 	<li>Good understanding of indexing tools such as Sphinx and working with large databases.</li>\n 	<li>Experience building web applications that are highly optimized for client/server performance</li>\n 	<li>Understanding of A/B testing and data driven development</li>\n 	<li>Reference-able systems that you have designed, developed and maintained through many development cycles</li>\n 	<li>6+ years experience</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Additional Information</h2>\n<h3>Benefits:</h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>401k, Health care though Trinet</li>\n 	<li>Awesome office location in downtown Los Altos, CA</li>\n 	<li>Great team!</li>\n</ul>','Senior Full Stack engineer and Team Lead','','publish','closed','closed','','senior-full-stack-engineer-and-team-lead','','','2017-04-23 02:15:57','2017-04-23 02:15:57','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=career&amp;p=1653',1,'career','',0),
	(1672,4,'2017-04-23 02:22:57','2017-04-23 02:22:57','<h2>Company Description</h2>\n\nCome help us change the real estate industry! We are a profitable, high-growth company that uses predictive analytics to identify hyper-targeted audiences for the delivery of advanced digital marketing for the real estate and lending industries.\n\nProspectNow allows you to identify owners whose properties are expected to sell and/or refinance in the next 12 months and hyper-targets these owners by displaying digital ads directly to these owners at their home on any connected device.\n\nThis hyper-targeted approach to marketing minimizes wasted marketing spend, increases your ROI, and engages you with your targets earlier in their decision process.\n\nAlong with the contact information of nearly every commercial and residential property owner in the United States, ProspectNow gets you to these decision makers of these properties faster.  An integrated CRM, dialer and mailing tools create the most effective prospecting and marketing platform in the industry. The largest Commercial and Residential Real Estate brokerages, lenders, property management companies and Fortune 500 companies all call ProspectNow a partner.  If you want to be part of an explosive growth and entrepreneurial environment, this is a tremendous opportunity. ProspectNow also has a great working environment and located right downtown in Los Altos. You will be a key player at a fast growing company, you will be challenged and you will have a lot of fun along the way. Come join the ProspectNow Team!\n\n<h2>Job Description</h2>\n\nDigital Advertising Sales Representative is responsible for prospecting, forecasting, reporting, booking and account management of ProspectNow IP Targeting Display Advertising Solutions to designated Named Accounts - Lending. Named Accounts - Lending will be designated by the General Manager.\n\nYou will establish and foster relationships across media, marketing, and analytics stakeholders to ensure strong ties at multiple levels, including higher level relationships to develop ongoing budget allocation expansion and upsell opportunities.\n\nAs an integral part of the Sales team, this role will be responsible for educating lenders about the value of ProspectNow Digital products and making recommendations how they can best be leveraged to achieve specific client goals and objectives.\n\nPlay a key role on the ProspectNow Sales team, selling display advertising products into high-value Lender/Banking accounts.\n\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>2+ years online advertising , digital media, or analytics sales experience with National accounts</li>\n<li>Must have significant success in media sales, with a specific focus on digital display/PPC Campaigns</li>\n<li>Experience selling audience targeting solutions</li>\n<li>Must have a demonstrable track record of commercial success and revenue growth</li>\n<li>Must have extensive experience of (and be passionate about) building and growing successful relationships with lenders</li>\n<li>Strong consultative sales skills, relationship building, external and internal customer satisfaction management</li>\n<li>Strong understanding of internet advertising technologies</li>\n<li>Ability to partner with internal stakeholders, including Account Management, to provide the best possible experience for our clients</li>\n<li>Self-starter capable of thriving in a growth stage company environment</li>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree</li>\n<li>Track record of building and maintaining strong client relationships and closing new business</li>\n<li>Positive \'No Quit\' attitude</li>\n<li>Fearless on the phones, persistent, and good work ethic</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Salesforce.com, google apps, join.me/gotomeeting a plus</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Additional Information</h2>\n\n<h3>Benefits:</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Uncapped commissions</li>\n<li>401(k), healthcare, vision, life insurance</li>\n<li>Convenient office location in downtown Los Altos, CA</li>\n<li>Great team!</li>\n</ul>','Digital Advertising Sales Representative','','publish','closed','closed','','digital-advertising-sales-representative','','','2017-04-23 02:22:57','2017-04-23 02:22:57','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=career&amp;p=1661',2,'career','',0),
	(1673,4,'2017-04-23 02:25:14','2017-04-23 02:25:14','<h2>Company Description</h2>\n\nCome help us change the real estate industry! We are a venture-backed, profitable, high-growth company that analyzes and predicts which properties that are most likely to sell.  Along with the contact information of nearly every commercial and residential property owner in the United States, ProspectNow gets you to these decision makers of these properties faster.  An integrated CRM, dialer and mailing tools create the most effective prospecting platform in the industry. The largest Commercial and Residential Real Estate brokerages, lenders, property management companies and Fortune 500 companies all call ProspectNow a partner.  If you want to be part of an explosive growth and entrepreneurial environment, this is a tremendous opportunity. ProspectNow also has a great working environment and located right downtown in Los Altos. You will be a key player at a fast growing company, you will be challenged and you will have a lot of fun along the way. Come join the ProspectNow Team!\n\n<h2>Job Description</h2>\n\nProspectNow.com is looking for highly motivated sales people to sell subscriptions of its Cloud-Based Commercial Real Estate Prospecting Platform to the enterprise. This role is critical and you will have a significant amount of responsibility. You would be conducting outreach to banks, real estate brokers, and lenders. Your responsibilities will include making outbound calls to executives, identifying the needs of the customer, mapping out who the decision makers are, conducting demonstrations and presentations to the decision makers, and managing the process to a successful closing. Your organizational skills and ability to manage up to 30 sales cycles at the same time is critical.\n\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Proven ability to navigate large organizations to identify key players and decision makers</li>\n<li>Experience in a Quota Carrying Role with a track record of over achievement</li>\n<li>Fearless on the phones, persistent, and good work ethic</li>\n<li>Minimum 3 years of sales experience in Saas or Software sales</li>\n<li>Positive \'No Quit\' attitude</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Salesforce.com, google apps, etc</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Commercial Real Estate or Commercial Banking is a plus</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Additional Information</h2>\n\n<h3>Benefits:</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Uncapped commissions</li>\n<li>401(k), healthcare, vision, life insurance</li>\n<li>Convenient office location in downtown Los Altos, CA</li>\n<li>Great team!</li>\n</ul>','Enterprise Sales Rep','','publish','closed','closed','','enterprise-sales-rep','','','2017-04-23 02:25:14','2017-04-23 02:25:14','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=career&amp;p=1665',3,'career','',0),
	(1674,4,'2017-04-23 02:27:11','2017-04-23 02:27:11','<h2>Company Description</h2>\n\nCome help us change the real estate industry! ProspectNow.com is a venture backed, profitable, high growth company that provides a nationwide database of 8 million commercial building owners to companies that need to contact and market to commercial building owners. We have over a thousand customers including fortune 500 companies as well as commercial real estate agents, lenders, and investors. If you want to be part of an explosive growth and entrepreneurial environment, this is a tremendous opportunity. ProspectNow also has a great working environment and located right downtown in Los Altos. You will be a key player at a fast growing company, you will be challenged and you will have a lot of fun along the way. Come join the ProspectNow Team!\n\n<h2>Job Description</h2>\n\nProspectNow.com is looking for highly motivated sales people to sell online subscriptions of its Cloud Based Commercial Real Estate database. ProspectNow.com is growing at an explosive rate. This role is critical and you will have a significant amount of responsibility. You would be conducting outreach to commercial real estate brokers and agents. Your responsibilities will include making outbound calls to executives, identifying the needs of the customer, mapping out who the decision makers are, conducting demonstrations and presentations to the decision makers, and managing the process to a successful closing. Your organizational skills and ability to manage up to 30 sales cycles at the same time is critical.\n\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Fearless on the phones, persistent, and good work ethic</li>\n<li>Experience in a Quota Carrying Role</li>\n<li>Minimum 1 years of sales experience in Saas or Software sales</li>\n<li>Positive \'No Quit\' attitude</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Salesforce.com, google apps, join.me/gotomeeting a plus</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Commercial Real Estate a plus</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Additional Information</h2>\n\nThe key to your success will be your ability to make calls to large numbers of leads and conduct demonstrations of the product over the internet. 50 calls per day is a minimum requirement. You will be given access to the latest marketing tools and sales automation technology including Salesforce.com and Insidesales.com dialing technology. ProspectNow will train you on the most effective sales techniques as well as the commercial real estate industry knowledge.','Inside Sales Rep','','publish','closed','closed','','inside-sales-rep','','','2017-04-23 02:27:11','2017-04-23 02:27:11','',0,'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=career&amp;p=1668',4,'career','',0),
